<subSubSection id="32DB655EDF5A4B04FF43F8A6DB8E4BFD" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="366" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" type="description">
<paragraph id="7A7E36D5DF5A4B05FF43F8A6D9B24A56" blockId="6.[151,1437,1820,2025]" box="[151,746,1820,1845]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5A4B05FF43F8A6DBAC4A57" bold="true" box="[151,244,1820,1845]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Length.</emphasis>
Male: 
<quantity id="BD399B30DF5A4B05FE97F8A6DAC14A56" box="[323,409,1820,1844]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
(n=5); female: 
<quantity id="BD399B30DF5A4B05FD93F8A6D9C54A56" box="[583,669,1820,1844]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1" pageId="6" pageNumber="365" unit="mm" value="3.1">3.1 mm</quantity>
(n=4).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A7E36D5DF5A4B05FF13F8FADEC44A3A" blockId="6.[151,1437,1820,2025]" box="[199,1436,1856,1881]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5A4B05FF13F8FADA394A3B" bold="true" box="[199,353,1856,1881]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Morphology.</emphasis>
Crown longer than distance between eyes (
<figureCitation id="E2FA2A50DF5A4B05FC91F8FAD8DF4A3A" box="[837,903,1856,1881]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,925,947]" captionTargetBox="[238,1350,209,894]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,193,916]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. male: A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C. face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376444/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
A). Male anteclypeus tapered distally (
<figureCitation id="E2FA2A50DF5A4B05FAE3F8FADE224A3A" box="[1335,1402,1856,1881]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,250,925,947]" captionTargetBox="[238,1350,209,894]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,193,916]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. male: A, habitus, dorsal view; B, habitus, lateral view; C. face." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376444/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7A7E36D5DF5A4B05FF13F8DEDA944A8A" blockId="6.[151,1437,1820,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5A4B05FF13F8DEDA214A1F" bold="true" box="[199,377,1892,1917]" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Subgenital plate long, lateral margin distinctly concave (
<figureCitation id="E2FA2A50DF5A4B05FBD4F8DEDF1C4A1E" box="[1024,1092,1892,1917]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[241,1352,1015,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,996,1906]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376445/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
C). Style with articulating arm short; preapical lobe rectangular; apophysis thick fingerlike, apex subtruncate (
<figureCitation id="E2FA2A50DF5A4B05FBC8F832DF384AC2" box="[1052,1120,1928,1953]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[241,1352,1015,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,996,1906]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376445/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
D). Connective shorter than aedeagus. Aedeagus slender, tapered from base to apex, curved dorsad with pair of slender apical appendages directed distad (
<figureCitation id="E2FA2A50DF5A4B05FE9EF86ADAD34A8A" box="[330,395,2000,2025]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[241,1352,1015,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,996,1906]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376445/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="365">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
E–F).
</paragraph>
<caption id="2EBE665DDF5B4B04FF43FA04DA4F4B73" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376443/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" targetBox="[216,1379,220,1421]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="7A7E36D5DF5B4B04FF43FA04DA4F4B73" blockId="7.[151,1436,1470,1553]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5B4B04FF43FA04DA4C48B1" bold="true" box="[151,276,1470,1492]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">FIGURE 6.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="BDC14D56DF5B4B04FEC9FA05DAE948B6" box="[285,433,1470,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cortona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="silvai" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5B4B04FEC9FA05DAE948B6" box="[285,433,1470,1492]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Cortona silvai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="538657BCDF5B4B04FE6DFA05DAAC48B6" box="[441,500,1471,1492]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" rank="species">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5B4B04FE6DFA05DAAC48B6" bold="true" box="[441,500,1471,1492]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X–XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="7A7E36D5DF5B4B04FF13F984DB8E4BFD" blockId="7.[151,1437,1598,1947]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5B4B04FF13F984DAF84B35" bold="true" box="[199,416,1598,1623]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Female abdomen.</emphasis>
Sternite VII with median lobe covering approximately two-thirds of posterior margin, trilobed, median lobe slightly narrower and more produced than lateral lobes, with dark pigment indistinct (
<figureCitation id="E2FA2A50DF5B4B04FABBF9D8DBEA4BFD" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1279,1301]" captionTargetBox="[208,1368,205,1232]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[188,1398,193,1258]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 11. Females of Cortona: A – D, Cortona minuta: A, first valvula; B, detail of first valvula apex; C, second valvula; D, third valvula. E – I, abdominal sternite VII: E, C. minuta; F, C. catanachae; G, C. silvai; H, C. otamendiensis; I, C. concordica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376448/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
H).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
