<subSubSection id="32DB655EDF5B4B04FF13F880D8AE4A31" box="[199,1014,1850,1875]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="7A7E36D5DF5B4B04FF13F880D8AE4A31" blockId="7.[151,1437,1598,1947]" box="[199,1014,1850,1875]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5B4B04FF13F880DA164A31" bold="true" box="[199,334,1850,1875]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is an adjective derived from the 
<typeStatus id="A57A8877DF5B4B04FCE7F880D8CD4A31" box="[819,917,1850,1875]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">holotype</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="32DB655EDF5B4B04FF13F8E4DECA4AF9" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7A7E36D5DF5B4B04FF13F8E4DECA4AF9" blockId="7.[151,1437,1598,1947]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5B4B04FF13F8E4DA634A15" bold="true" box="[199,315,1886,1911]" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is readily distinguishable from all others within 
<taxonomicName id="BDC14D56DF5B4B04FC3DF8E5DF1E4A14" box="[1001,1094,1887,1910]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Cortona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="366" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="48B5EAC7DF5B4B04FC3DF8E5DF1E4A14" box="[1001,1094,1887,1910]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Cortona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the aedeagus with a pair of short apical appendages directed apicad, and shaft curved 70° dorsad with a slim apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation id="E2FA2A50DF5B4B04FAC4F838DE0A4AF9" box="[1296,1362,1922,1947]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[241,1352,1015,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[226,1360,996,1906]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 8. Cortona otamendiensis sp. n. A, male pygofer lobe, lateral view; B, male pygofer and segments X – XI, dorsal view; C, valve and subgenital plate, ventral view; D, style, dorsal view; E, F, connective and aedeagus, dorsal and lateral view, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/376445/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="366">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
E–F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
